The paper discusses the use of interactive visualization and requirements traceability concepts to support the validation of formal models in engineering disciplines. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category, as it deals with the development processes and tool support for formal modeling. Additionally, the use of interactive visualization implies a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC), while the use of formal models suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to Programming Languages (cs.PL), as it discusses the use of formal models in the context of railway operations.
